        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 2:43PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 243 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Indian Mills, or near Pipestem, moving southeast
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...

Locations impacted include...
Pipestem...
Red Sulphur Spring...
Buck...
Wayside...
Indian Mills...
Pipestem Resort State Park...
and Bozoo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
